      <h1>Montessori School Melkbos: What Makes Lily House Unique on the West Coast</h1>
      <p class="subtitle" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">April 28, 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1580582932707-520aed937b7b?w=1200&q=80" alt="Lily House Melkbos campus" style="width:100%;border-radius:1rem;margin-bottom:2rem;" />

      <p>Nestled along the stunning West Coast, Lily House Melkbos offers a unique Montessori education that blends coastal charm with academic excellence. Under the leadership of Principal Jess Hanafey, our Melkbos campus has become a beacon for families seeking an authentic Montessori experience in a nurturing, intimate environment.</p>

      <h2>What Sets Lily House Melkbos Apart</h2>

      <p>At Lily House Melkbos, we believe in education that honours the whole child. Our Montessori approach fosters independence, curiosity, and a lifelong love of learning. Here's what makes us unique:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Small class sizes</strong> — ensuring every child receives individualised attention</li>
        <li><strong>Experienced Montessori guides</strong> — led by Jess Hanafey, our 6-9 guide and campus principal</li>
        <li><strong>Coastal learning environment</strong> — our location on Van Riebeekstrand inspires a deep connection with nature</li>
        <li><strong>Pre-primary and primary programmes</strong> — serving children from 18 months through to 9 years</li>
      </ul>

      <p>We invite you to visit our Melkbos campus and experience the Lily House difference firsthand. Book a tour today and discover why we're the preferred Montessori school on the West Coast.</p>

      <div style="text-align:center;margin-top:3rem;">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-accent">Book a Tour</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

